Adolphe Bridge.label: Adolphe Bridge
Adolphe Bridge.description: Adolphe Bridge is an arch bridge in Luxembourg City, in southern Luxembourg. The bridge takes road traffic across the Pétrusse, connecting Boulevard Royal, in Ville Haute, to Avenue de la Liberté, in Gare. Wikipedia

Øresund Bridge.label: Øresund Bridge
Øresund Bridge.description: The Öresund or Øresund Bridge is a double-track railway and dual carriageway bridge-tunnel across the Øresund strait between Scania and Denmark. Wikipedia

Centennial Bridge, Panama.label: Centennial Bridge, Panama
Centennial Bridge, Panama.description: Panama's Centennial Bridge is a major bridge crossing the Panama Canal. It was built to supplement the overcrowded Bridge of the Americas and to replace it as the carrier of the Pan-American Highway. Wikipedia

Cannon Street Railway Bridge.label: Cannon Street Railway Bridge
Cannon Street Railway Bridge.description: Cannon Street Railway Bridge is a bridge in central London, crossing the River Thames. Downstream, the next bridge is London Bridge, and upstream Southwark Bridge. It carries trains over the river to Cannon Street station on the north bank. Wikipedia

Chelsea Bridge.label: Chelsea Bridge
Chelsea Bridge.description: Chelsea Bridge is a bridge over the River Thames in west London, connecting Chelsea on the north bank to Battersea on the south bank. There have been two Chelsea Bridges, on the site of what was an ancient ford. Wikipedia

Colemanville Covered Bridge.label: Colemanville Covered Bridge
Colemanville Covered Bridge.description: The Colemanville Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans Pequea Creek in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. After Hunsecker's Mill Covered Bridge, it is Lancaster County's second-longest single-span covered bridge still being used. Wikipedia

Fehmarn Sound Bridge.label: Fehmarn Sound Bridge
Fehmarn Sound Bridge.description: The Fehmarn Sound Bridge connects the German island of Fehmarn in the Baltic Sea with the German mainland near Großenbrode. Wikipedia

Grosvenor Bridge.label: Grosvenor Bridge
Grosvenor Bridge.description: Grosvenor Bridge, originally known as, and alternatively called Victoria Railway Bridge, is a railway bridge over the River Thames in London, between Vauxhall Bridge and Chelsea Bridge. Wikipedia

Hangzhou Bay Bridge.label: Hangzhou Bay Bridge
Hangzhou Bay Bridge.description: Hangzhou Bay Bridge is a highway bridge with a cable-stayed portion across Hangzhou Bay in the eastern coastal region of China. It connects the municipalities of Jiaxing and Ningbo in Zhejiang province. Wikipedia

Hörn Bridge.label: Hörn Bridge
Hörn Bridge.description: The Hörn Bridge is a folding bridge in the city of Kiel in the German state of Schleswig-Holstein. The bridge spans over the end of the Kiel Fjord and was designed by Gerkan, Marg and Partners. Wikipedia

Hohenzollern Bridge.label: Hohenzollern Bridge
Hohenzollern Bridge.description: The Hohenzollern Bridge is a bridge crossing the river Rhine in the German city of Cologne. It crosses the Rhine at kilometre 688.5. Wikipedia

Herr's Mill Covered Bridge.label: Herr's Mill Covered Bridge
Herr's Mill Covered Bridge.description:
The Herr's Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans Pequea Creek in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. It is also sometimes known as Soudersburg Bridge.
The bridge has a double span, wooden, double Burr arch trusses design. Wikipedia

Hunsecker's Mill Covered Bridge.label: Hunsecker's Mill Covered Bridge
Hunsecker's Mill Covered Bridge.description: The Hunsecker's Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge located in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. The bridge has a single span, wooden, double Burr arch trusses design. Wikipedia

Interstate Bridge.label: Interstate Bridge
Interstate Bridge.description: The Interstate Bridge is a pair of nearly identical steel vertical-lift, "Parker type" through-truss bridges that carry Interstate 5 traffic over the Columbia River between Vancouver, Washington and Portland, Oregon in the United States. Wikipedia

Jack Pesch Bridge.label: Jack Pesch Bridge
Jack Pesch Bridge.description: The Jack Pesch Bridge is a bridge for pedestrians and cyclists which crosses the Brisbane River. The bridge is named in honour of Jack Pesch, a cycling champion during the 1930s. Wikipedia

Karni crossing.label: Karni crossing
Karni crossing.description: The Karni Crossing was a cargo terminal on the Israel-Gaza Strip barrier. It is located in the north-eastern end of the Gaza Strip and was opened in 1994 after the signing of the Oslo Accords, in order ... Wikipedia

Keller's Mill Covered Bridge.label: Keller's Covered Bridge
Keller's Mill Covered Bridge.description: The Keller's Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans Cocalico Creek in Ephrata Township, Lancaster County in the US state of Pennsylvania. A county-owned and maintained bridge, its official designation is the Cocalico No. 5 Bridge. Wikipedia

Krk Bridge.label: Krk Bridge
Krk Bridge.description: Krk Bridge is a 1430 m long reinforced concrete arch bridge connecting the Croatian island of Krk to the mainland and carrying over a million vehicles per year. Wikipedia

Krka Bridge.label: Krka Bridge
Krka Bridge.description: The Krka Bridge is located in Croatia, between the Skradin and Šibenik interchanges. It is a 391 metres long concrete arch bridge spanning the Krka River at a height of 65 metres. Wikipedia

Kurtz's Mill Covered Bridge.label: Kurtz's Mill Covered Bridge
Kurtz's Mill Covered Bridge.description: The Kurtz's Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans Mill Creek in the Lancaster County Park in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. Wikipedia

Lambeth Bridge.label: Lambeth Bridge
Lambeth Bridge.description: Lambeth Bridge is a road traffic and footbridge crossing the River Thames in an east-west direction in central London, the river flows north at the crossing point. Wikipedia

Landis Mill Covered Bridge.label: Landis Mill Covered Bridge
Landis Mill Covered Bridge.description: The Landis Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans the Little Conestoga Creek in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. A county-owned and maintained bridge, its official designation is the Little Conestoga #1 Bridge. Wikipedia

Leonard P. Zakim Bunker Hill Memorial Br.label: Leonard P. Zakim Bunker Hill Memorial Bridge
Leonard P. Zakim Bunker Hill Memorial Br.description: The Leonard P. Zakim Bunker Hill Memorial Bridge is a cable-stayed bridge across the Charles River in Boston, Massachusetts. It is a replacement for the Charlestown High Bridge, an older truss bridge constructed in the 1950s. Wikipedia

Mark Clark Bridge.label: Mark Clark Bridge
Mark Clark Bridge.description: The Mark Clark Bridge, built in 1949, carried Washington State Route 532 across the Stillaguamish River to connect Stanwood, Washington to Camano Island. It provided the only road access to the island. Wikipedia

Merivale Bridge.label: Merivale Bridge
Merivale Bridge.description: The Merivale Bridge is a double track railway bridge crossing the Brisbane River. It crosses the Milton Reach of the river, slightly to the west of the William Jolly Bridge. Wikipedia

Pinetown Bushong's Mill Covered Bridge.label: Pinetown Covered Bridge
Pinetown Bushong's Mill Covered Bridge.description: The Pinetown Bushong's Mill Covered Bridge is a covered bridge that spans the Conestoga River in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania, United States. A county-owned and maintained bridge, its official designation is the Big Conestoga #6 Bridge. Wikipedia

Netafim Border Crossing.label: Netafim Border Crossing
Netafim Border Crossing.description: The Netafim Crossing is a border crossing between Israel and Egypt. It is located adjacent to Highway 12, about 12 km north of Eilat, 1 km north west of Ein Netafim. Wikipedia

Pons Sublicius.label: Pons Sublicius
Pons Sublicius.description: The earliest known bridge of ancient Rome, Italy, the Pons Sublicius, spanned the Tiber River near the Forum Boarium downstream from the Tiber Island, near the foot of the Aventine Hill. Wikipedia

Pons Fabricius.label: Pons Fabricius
Pons Fabricius.description: The Pons Fabricius or Ponte dei Quattro Capi, is the oldest Roman bridge in Rome, Italy, still existing in its original state. Built in 62 BC, it spans half of the Tiber River, from the Campus Martius on the east side to Tiber Island in the middle. Wikipedia

Pont Mirabeau.label: Pont Mirabeau
Pont Mirabeau.description: The pont Mirabeau was built between 1895 and 1897. It was listed a historical monument in 1975. Wikipedia

Pont Neuf.label: Pont Neuf
Pont Neuf.description: The Pont Neuf is the oldest standing bridge across the river Seine in Paris, France. Its name, which was given to distinguish it from older bridges that were lined on both sides with houses, has remained. Wikipedia

Pont de Normandie.label: Pont de Normandie
Pont de Normandie.description: The Pont de Normandie is a cable-stayed road bridge that spans the river Seine linking Le Havre to Honfleur in Normandy, northern France. Its total length is 2,143.21 metres – 856 metres between the two piers. Wikipedia

Pont National.label: Pont National
Pont National.description: The pont National is a road and rail bridge across the Seine in Paris, to the east of the XIIe and XIIIe arrondissements. With a total length of 188.5m, it is made up of 5 masonry arches. Wikipedia

Pont d'Arcole.label: Pont d'Arcole
Pont d'Arcole.description: The Pont d'Arcole is a bridge in Paris over the River Seine. It is served by the Metro station Hôtel de Ville. Wikipedia

Pons Aemilius.label: Pons Aemilius
Pons Aemilius.description: The Pons Aemilius, today called Ponte Rotto, is the oldest Roman stone bridge in Rome, Italy. Preceded by a wooden version, it was rebuilt in stone in the 2nd century BC. Wikipedia

Pont du Diable (Céret).label: Pont du Diable
Pont du Diable (Céret).description: The Pont du Diable or Pont Vieux is a medieval stone arch bridge at Céret, France, built between 1321 and 1341. Spanning the river Tech with an imposing single arch of 45.45 m span length. Wikipedia

Pont du Garigliano.label: Pont du Garigliano
Pont du Garigliano.description: The Pont du Garigliano is a bridge across the Seine in Paris. Wikipedia

Seven Mile Bridge.label: Seven Mile Bridge
Seven Mile Bridge.description: The Seven Mile Bridge is a famous bridge in the Florida Keys, in Monroe County, Florida, United States. It connects Knight's Key in the Middle Keys to Little Duck Key in the Lower Keys. Wikipedia

Skye Bridge.label: Skye Bridge
Skye Bridge.description: The Skye Bridge is a road bridge over Loch Alsh, Scotland, connecting the Isle of Skye to the island of Eilean Bàn. The name is also used for the whole Skye Crossing, which further connects Eilean Bàn to the mainland across the Carrich Viaduct. Wikipedia

Svatopluk Čech Bridge.label: Svatopluk Čech Bridge
Svatopluk Čech Bridge.description:
Svatopluk Čech Bridge or Čech Bridge is an arch bridge over river Vltava in Prague, Czech Republic.
Construction of the bridge started in 1905 and finished in 1908. Its length is 169 m and width is 16 m. Wikipedia

Royal Gorge Bridge.label: Royal Gorge Bridge
Royal Gorge Bridge.description: The Royal Gorge Bridge is a tourist attraction near Cañon City, Colorado, within Royal Gorge Bridge & Park, a 360-acre theme park. Wikipedia

Tay Rail Bridge.label: Tay Rail Bridge
Tay Rail Bridge.description:
The Tay Rail Bridge carries the main-line railway across the Firth of Tay in Scotland, between the city of Dundee and the suburb of Wormit in Fife. Its span is 2.75 miles.
The present-day structure is the second one on its site. Wikipedia

Vasco da Gama Bridge.label: Vasco da Gama Bridge
Vasco da Gama Bridge.description: The Vasco da Gama Bridge is a cable-stayed bridge flanked by viaducts and rangeviews that spans the Tagus River in Parque das Nações in Lisbon, capital of Portugal. Wikipedia

Waterloo Bridge.label: Waterloo Bridge
Waterloo Bridge.description: At the onset of World War I, British officer Roy Cronin (Robert Taylor) and ballerina Myra (Vivien Leigh) meet and fall in love. As fate would have it, Cronin is called to active duty shortly thereafter. When Cronin's departure coincides with a performance, Myra chooses to skip the ballet to see her… More love leave. As a result, she is dismissed from the ballet and struggles to make ends meet -- and when she reads of Cronin's misreported death, Myra hits rock bottom, resorting to prostitution.

London Bridge.label: London Bridge
London Bridge.description: London Bridge refers to several historical bridges that have spanned the River Thames between the City of London and Southwark, in central London. Wikipedia

Wiesen Viaduct.label: Wiesen Viaduct
Wiesen Viaduct.description: The Wiesen Viaduct is a single track limestone railway viaduct. It spans the Landwasser River southwest of the hamlet of Wiesen, in the Canton of Graubünden, Switzerland. Wikipedia

Victoria Bridge, Brisbane.label: Victoria Bridge, Brisbane
Victoria Bridge, Brisbane.description: The Victoria Bridge is a vehicular and pedestrian bridge over the Brisbane River. The current bridge, opened in 1969, is the third permanent crossing erected at this location. It is shared by vehicular traffic, pedestrians and cyclists. Wikipedia

Petit Pont.label: Petit Pont
Petit Pont.description: The Petit Pont is a bridge crossing the River Seine in Paris, built in 1853, although a structure has crossed the river at this point since antiquity. Wikipedia

Pont Marie.label: Pont Marie
Pont Marie.description:
The Pont Marie is a bridge which crosses the Seine in Paris, France.
The bridge links the Île Saint-Louis to the quai de l'Hôtel de Ville and is one of three bridges designed to allow traffic flow ... Wikipedia

Bridge of the Americas.label: Bridge of the Americas
Bridge of the Americas.description: The Bridge of the Americas is a road bridge in Panama, which spans the Pacific entrance to the Panama Canal. Wikipedia

Pont amont.label: Pont amont
Pont amont.description: The Pont Amont is a bridge in Paris which carries the Boulevard Périphérique over the Seine River. Entirely dedicated to motor traffic, it is the first bridge to be seen when following the Seine downstream into Paris. Wikipedia

Pont aval.label: Pont aval
Pont aval.description: The Pont Aval is a bridge that crosses the Seine in Paris, France. It is open exclusively to motor vehicles traveling along the Boulevard Périphérique, a roadway which encircles the city. Wikipedia

Pont de Bercy.label: Pont de Bercy
Pont de Bercy.description:
The Pont de Bercy is a bridge over the Seine in Paris, France.
The structure links the 12th and 13th arrondissements of Paris by extending the Boulevard de Bercy and the Boulevard Vincent-Auriol. Wikipedia

Pont des Arts.label: Pont des Arts
Pont des Arts.description: The Pont des Arts or Passerelle des Arts is a pedestrian bridge in Paris which crosses the Seine River. It links the Institut de France and the central square of the palais du Louvre,. Wikipedia

Pont de l'Archevêché.label: Pont de l'Archevêché
Pont de l'Archevêché.description: The Pont de l'Archevêché is a bridge crossing the Seine river in Paris, France. Wikipedia

Pont des Invalides.label: Pont des Invalides
Pont des Invalides.description: The Pont des Invalides is the lowest bridge traversing the Seine in Paris. Wikipedia

Ponte Vecchio.label: Ponte Vecchio
Ponte Vecchio.description: The Ponte Vecchio is a Medieval stone closed-spandrel segmental arch bridge over the Arno River, in Florence, Italy, noted for still having shops built along it, as was once common. Wikipedia

Southwark Bridge.label: Southwark Bridge
Southwark Bridge.description: Southwark Bridge is an arch bridge in London, England, for traffic linking the district of Southwark and the City across the River Thames. Wikipedia

Kessock Bridge.label: Kessock Bridge
Kessock Bridge.description: The Kessock Bridge carries the A9 trunk road across the Beauly Firth at Inverness. Wikipedia

Triple Bridge.label: Triple Bridge
Triple Bridge.description: The Triple Bridge is a group of three bridges across the Ljubljanica River. It connects the Ljubljana's historical, medieval, town on one bank, and the modern city of Ljubljana, capital of Slovenia, on the other. Wikipedia

Stari Most.label: Stari Most
Stari Most.description: Stari Most is a reconstruction of a 16th-century Ottoman bridge in the city of Mostar in Bosnia and Herzegovina that crosses the river Neretva and connects two parts of the city. Wikipedia

Tamar Bridge.label: Tamar Bridge
Tamar Bridge.description: The Tamar Bridge is a major road bridge at Saltash in southwest England carrying traffic between Cornwall and Devon over the River Tamar. When it opened in 1961 it was the longest suspension bridge in the United Kingdom. Wikipedia

Tyne Bridge.label: Tyne Bridge
Tyne Bridge.description: The Tyne Bridge is a through arch bridge over the River Tyne in North East England, linking Newcastle upon Tyne and Gateshead. Wikipedia

Sandnessund Bridge.label: Sandnessund Bridge
Sandnessund Bridge.description: Sandnessund Bridge is a cantilever road bridge that crosses the Sandnessundet strait between the islands of Tromsøya and Kvaløya in the municipality of Tromsø in Troms county, Norway. Wikipedia

Andøy Bridge.label: Andøy Bridge
Andøy Bridge.description: Andøy Bridge is a cantilever road bridge that crosses the Risøysundet strait between the islands of Andøya and Hinnøya in Nordland county, Norway. The northern end of the bridge is located in the village of Risøyhamn. Wikipedia

Demidov Bridge.label: Demidov Bridge
Demidov Bridge.description: The Demidov Bridge is a bridge across the Griboyedov Canal in Saint Petersburg, Russia. It connects Kazansky and Spassky islands. Wikipedia

Maribyrnong River Viaduct.label: Maribyrnong River Viaduct
Maribyrnong River Viaduct.description: The Maribyrnong River Viaduct caries the Albion–Jacana railway line, Melbourne across the Maribyrnong River in the western suburbs of Melbourne, Australia. It is located near the E.J. Whitten Bridge, and almost 400 metres long. Wikipedia

Triborough Bridge.label: Triborough Bridge
Triborough Bridge.description: The Triborough Bridge, renamed the Robert F. Kennedy Bridge in 2008, and sometimes referred to as the RFK Triborough Bridge, is a complex of three separate bridges in New York City, United States, ... Wikipedia

Wills Creek Bollman Bridge.label: Wills Creek Bollman Bridge
Wills Creek Bollman Bridge.description: The Wills Creek Bollman Bridge originally served the Baltimore and Ohio Railroad's Pittsburgh Division main line. Wikipedia

Sixth Street Bridge (Grand Rapids, Michi.label: Sixth Street Bridge
Sixth Street Bridge (Grand Rapids, Michi.description: The Sixth Street Bridge is a four-span, wrought iron bridge that crosses the Grand River in Grand Rapids, Michigan. It is a Michigan State Historic Site and is listed on the National Register of Historic Places. Wikipedia

14th Street Bridge (Potomac River).label: 14th Street Bridge
14th Street Bridge (Potomac River).description: The 14th Street Bridge is a complex of five bridges across the Potomac River, connecting Arlington, Virginia, with Washington, D.C. Wikipedia

10th Avenue Bridge.label: 10th Avenue Bridge
10th Avenue Bridge.description: The 10th Avenue Bridge crosses the Mississippi River near downtown Minneapolis, Minnesota and also in proximity to the University of Minnesota. Wikipedia

Ada Bridge.label: Ada Bridge
Ada Bridge.description: The Ada bridge or alternatively Sava bridge is a cable-stayed bridge over the Sava river in Belgrade, Serbia. The bridge crosses the tip of Ada Ciganlija island, connecting the municipalities of Čukarica and New Belgrade. Wikipedia

Antioch Bridge.label: Antioch Bridge
Antioch Bridge.description: The Antioch Bridge crosses the San Joaquin River linking Antioch, California with Sacramento County, California, United States. The bridge is signed as part of State Route 160. Wikipedia

Arthur Ravenel Jr. Bridge.label: Arthur Ravenel Jr. Bridge
Arthur Ravenel Jr. Bridge.description:
Grace Memorial Bridge and Silas N. Pearman Bridge.
The Arthur Ravenel Jr. Bridge, also known as the New Cooper River Bridge, is a cable-stayed bridge over the Cooper River in South Carolina, connecting downtown Charleston to Mount Pleasant. Wikipedia

Arkadiko Bridge.label: Arkadiko Bridge
Arkadiko Bridge.description: The Arkadiko Bridge or Kazarma Bridge is a Mycenaean bridge near the modern road from Tiryns to Epidauros on the Peloponnese, Greece. Dating to the Greek Bronze Age, it is one of the oldest arch bridges still in existence and use. Wikipedia

Balclutha Road Bridge.label: Balclutha Road Bridge
Balclutha Road Bridge.description: The Balclutha Road Bridge, which spans the Clutha River in Balclutha, South Otago, New Zealand, is one of the best-known road bridges in New Zealand's South Island. Wikipedia

Auckland Harbour Bridge.label: Auckland Harbour Bridge
Auckland Harbour Bridge.description: The Auckland Harbour Bridge is an eight-lane box truss motorway bridge over the Waitemata Harbour, joining St Marys Bay in Auckland with Northcote in the former North Shore City, New Zealand. Wikipedia

Battersea Railway Bridge.label: Battersea Railway Bridge
Battersea Railway Bridge.description: The Battersea Railway Bridge - properly called the Cremorne Bridge, after the pleasure grounds in Chelsea and originally commonly referred to as the Battersea New Bridge - is a bridge across the River ... Wikipedia

Band-e Kaisar.label: Band-e Kaisar
Band-e Kaisar.description: The Band-e Kaisar, Pol-e Kaisar, Bridge of Valerian or Shadirwan was an ancient arch bridge in Shushtar, Iran, and the first in the country to combine it with a dam. Wikipedia

Berwick Bridge.label: Berwick Bridge
Berwick Bridge.description: Berwick Bridge, also known as the Old Bridge, spans the River Tweed in Berwick-upon-Tweed, Northumberland, England. The current structure is a Grade I listed stone bridge built between 1611 and 1624. Wikipedia

Big Four Bridge.label: Big Four Bridge
Big Four Bridge.description: The Big Four Bridge is a six-span former railroad truss bridge that crosses the Ohio River, connecting Louisville, Kentucky, and Jeffersonville, Indiana, United States. It was completed in 1895, and updated in 1929. Wikipedia

Bill Emerson Memorial Bridge.label: Bill Emerson Memorial Bridge
Bill Emerson Memorial Bridge.description: The Bill Emerson Memorial Bridge is a cable-stayed bridge connecting Missouri's Route 34 and Route 74 with Illinois Route 146 across the Mississippi River between Cape Girardeau, Missouri and East Cape Girardeau, Illinois. Wikipedia

Broadway Bridge (Portland).label: Broadway Bridge
Broadway Bridge (Portland).description: The Broadway Bridge is a Rall-type bascule bridge spanning the Willamette River in Portland, Oregon, United States; Portland's first bascule bridge; intended and continues to hold the distinction of ... Wikipedia

Burlington Northern Railroad Bridge 5.1.label: Burlington Northern Railroad Bridge 5.1
Burlington Northern Railroad Bridge 5.1.description: The Burlington Northern Railroad Bridge 5.1 or BNSF Railway Bridge 5.1, also known as the St. Johns Railroad Bridge or the Willamette River Railroad Bridge, is a through truss railway bridge with a ... Wikipedia

Bronx–Whitestone Bridge.label: Bronx–Whitestone Bridge
Bronx–Whitestone Bridge.description: The Bronx–Whitestone Bridge is a suspension bridge in New York City that crosses the East River and connects the boroughs of Queens on Long Island and The Bronx via Interstate 678. Wikipedia

Canal Street railroad bridge.label: Canal Street railroad bridge
Canal Street railroad bridge.description: The Canal Street railroad bridge is a vertical-lift bridge across the south branch of the Chicago River in Chicago, Illinois. When it was constructed in 1914, its 1500-ton main span was the heaviest of any vertical lift bridge in the United States. Wikipedia

Carl Perkins Bridge.label: Carl Perkins Bridge
Carl Perkins Bridge.description: The Carl D. Perkins Bridge is a cantilever bridge that spans the Ohio River between Portsmouth, Ohio and Greenup County, Kentucky. The bridge carries the two lanes of State Route 852 and Truck Route U.S. Highway 23. Wikipedia

Charter Oak Bridge.label: Charter Oak Bridge
Charter Oak Bridge.description: The Charter Oak Bridge is one of the three highway bridges over the Connecticut River in Hartford, Connecticut. The twin steel stringer bridge carries the Wilbur Cross Highway and has an average daily traffic of 79,800. Wikipedia

Chengyang Bridge.label: Chengyang Bridge
Chengyang Bridge.description: Chengyang Bridge or Chengyang Wind and Rain Bridge, is a bridge in Sanjiang County, Liuzhou, Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, People's Republic of China. The bridge is in a Dong minority region. Wikipedia

Chesapeake Bay Bridge.label: Chesapeake Bay Bridge
Chesapeake Bay Bridge.description: The Chesapeake Bay Bridge is a major dual-span bridge in the U.S. state of Maryland. Spanning the Chesapeake Bay, it connects the state's rural Eastern Shore region with the more urban Western Shore. Wikipedia

City Island Bridge.label: City Island Bridge
City Island Bridge.description: The City Island Bridge is a bridge in the New York City borough of the Bronx, connecting City Island and Rodman's Neck on the mainland. It opened for traffic in 1901. Wikipedia

Cleddau Bridge.label: Cleddau BridgeCleddau Bridge Hotel
Cleddau Bridge.description: The Cleddau Bridge is a toll bridge on the A477 road that spans the River Cleddau between Neyland and Pembroke Dock, Wales. It was originally called the Milford Haven Bridge. Wikipedia

Conde McCullough Memorial Bridge.label: Conde McCullough Memorial Bridge
Conde McCullough Memorial Bridge.description: The Conde B. McCullough Memorial Bridge, formerly the North Bend Bridge, is a cantilever bridge that spans Coos Bay on U.S. Route 101 near North Bend, Oregon. Wikipedia

Crescent City Connection.label: Crescent City Connection
Crescent City Connection.description: The Crescent City Connection, formerly the Greater New Orleans Bridge, refers to twin cantilever bridges that carry U.S. Route 90 Business over the Mississippi River in New Orleans, Louisiana, United States. Wikipedia
